# M5-F6 a11y coverage manifest (R-A11Y-001) — the append-only shared anchor every M5 editor panel
# registers into. One JSON object per line (JSON Lines). A panel is "covered" only when it appears
# HERE and in registered_panels() (src/editor/gui/a11y/registry.cpp); tools/a11y_scan.py cross-checks
# the two on every PR. Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored. Concurrent M5 waves
# union-merge their appends (see .gitattributes: merge=union) — keep one panel per line so appends
# never collide. Fields: id (matches the registry id), title, owner (the task that added it),
# requires (the checks the panel must pass).
# `requires: ["ts-a11y"]` marks a ContentType::local panel (M9 e06d): editor-core renders it, so there
# is no C++ model for the harness to scan and its a11y gate lives in the `webui-ts-*` browser tier over
# the REAL DOM instead. gui-a11y-coverage requires that marker on exactly the local roster entries, and
# tools/a11y_scan.py exempts them from the scanned-set cross-check (they can never appear in it).
